  "notes": [
    "Datasheet: 137 pages, R01DS0466EJ0120 v1.20, Sep 2025.",
    "Single die with 8 orderable SKUs that toggle Mali-G31 GPU, Mali-C55 ISP (RZ/V2NP suffix), and security-crypto extensions on/off.  N41/N42/N45/N46 are RZ/V2N (no ISP); N43/N44/N47/N48 are RZ/V2NP (with ISP).",
    "DRP-AI: 4 dense TOPS, up to 15 sparse TOPS @ 1.0 GHz.  Vendor toolchain: DRP-AI translator + DRP-AI TVM.",
    "Quad Cortex-A55 @ 1.8 GHz @ 0.9 V (1.1 GHz @ 0.8 V low-power).  L3 cache max frequency is 1.26 GHz, not 1.8 GHz.",
    "VCD: H.264 1080p60 / H.265 4K30 encode + decode in hardware.",
    "Shipment suffix '#ACx' = individual tray, '#BCx' = full carton.  Variants with '#AC0' or '#BC0' do not support MIPI-DSI Display Command Set control.",
    "AC0 default per Alp Lab vendors/renesas-rzv2n/README.md — R9A09G056N44GBG#AC0 backs the E1M-V2N* and E1M-V2M* SoM SKUs.",
    "MIPI CSI-2 has 2 instances; MIPI DSI has 1.  PCIe Gen3 supports 1 or 2 lanes (no 4-lane on RZ/V2N — that's RZ/V2H).",
    "GPU and ISP are optional silicon and require software to detect them at runtime via the Renesas FSP.",
    "On the V2N-M1 SoM, the DeepX DX-M1 sits behind PCIe internally — see metadata/socs/deepx/dx/m1.json."
  ]
